[DQC.US.0195.10627] us-gaap:StockIssuedDuringPeriodValueShareBasedCompensation has a value of -2,000,000 and has been used with a retained earnings member. This element should not have a value when used with a retained earnings member. The preparer should consider if the value is input correctly or if a different element or member should be used.
This rule will not report an error if the Retained Earnings value is less than 10% of the total impacting shareholders equity. The total compared to determine materiality is 10% of 0 or 0.
